The formulation of a commercial revitalization program must be based on a thorough assessment of local needs and a
realistic program design. An important consideration is whether the proposed program is designed to be marketable
given income characteristics, local business condition, etc. The condition of supporting public facilities and
improvements and their influence on the business environment must be established. If public improvements are proposed
in connection with economic expansion or retention, applicants must address the extent to which the lack of these
