<SUMMARY>
SUMMARY:

 The Secretary announces priorities for four programs administered by the Office of Special Education and Rehabilitative
Services. The Secretary may use these priorities for competitions in fiscal year (FY) 1995 and subsequent years.
The Secretary takes this action to focus Federal financial assistance on areas of identified national need. These
priorities are intended to prepare individuals to enter rehabilitation professions and to maintain and upgrade
the basic skills and knowledge of trained rehabilitation professionals. 



</SUMMARY>
