 Six commenters expressed concern regarding the availability of training under this priority to direct service personnel
in rural areas, and several of these commenters recommended that projects under this priority be required to coordinate
training through existing programs in rural areas or use distance education strategies. 


Discussion:

 Projects funded under this priority are required to provide training for direct service personnel throughout a multi-State
geographical area. The use of distance education 
strategies and linkages with existing training programs serving rural areas is not precluded under this priority.



