 One commenter suggested that the priority be more responsive to individuals with disabilities by requiring the projects
funded under this priority to promote cooperation with local partnerships funded by the School-to-Work Opportunities
Act and with employment centers, and to include training in the evaluation of occupational and skill attainment.



Discussion:

 The Secretary believes that these activities are encouraged under the priority as projects are required to coordinate
