None.


Priority 3_Training Members of American Indian Tribes, State Vocational Rehabilitation Staff, and Rehabilitation
Educators on Services for American Indians With Disabilities 




Comments: 

One commenter expressed concern that the priority restricts training to States having high American Indian populations
when the needs of American Indians living in States with low populations are just as great. In addition, the commenter
indicated that, since the needs of these two groups are different, it will be difficult for States with low American
Indian populations to successfully replicate the training models developed. For these reasons, the commenter recommended
that the priority be opened to all States. 





